Firefighters and paramedics were called to the City Life building on Anton Lembede Street (Smith) where they discovered a thick column of smoke coming from one of the offices. According to paramedics from Rescue Care, a total of 18 people were treated for smoke inhalation and had to be taken to hospital. Authorities closed off Anton Lembede Street at the intersections of Dr Yusuf Dadoo Street (Grey) and Joseph Nduli Street (Russell).  To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
